      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what i was afraid of. it feels way more intentional than just \"personalization\" though. like, it's not just random, the timing of it feels way too specific to how i'm actually feeling in the moment. do u think they'd actually run tests on individual people like this? like using a regular household to see how well their affective algorithms work in a real-world setting?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
