      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what's so scary. if they are testing on people in their own homes, i wonder how they handle the privacy side of it. like, if they're using my actual emotional reactions to train their models, is there any way to even know they're doing it? or would it just look like \"smart\" features to anyone else?",
